`adjustResize` was deprecated in Android 11 and is no longer honored in .NET 10's edge-to-edge default. Here's the modern approach:

## Use keyboard insets to pad your layout

In your Android platform initialization (`Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`):

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
            Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of keyboard or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

## Chat page layout

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" />
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" Command="{Binding SendCommand}" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

**Why this works:** Instead of resizing the window (deprecated), you listen for IME (keyboard) insets via `WindowInsetsCompat` and apply bottom padding equal to the keyboard height. The input bar naturally rides above the keyboard.

**Tip:** If `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (on by default since .NET 8) interferes, disable it on your page:

```csharp
Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();
```

For **iOS**, `adjustResize` was never relevant — iOS handles this automatically via safe area insets, so no extra work is needed there.
